sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Discord User
    participant Main as Main Process
    participant LLM as OpenAI Realtime
    participant Sub as Subprocess
    participant YT as yt-dlp
    participant FF as ffmpeg
    participant DV as Discord Voice

    User->>Main: "Play a Future song" (voice turn)
    Main->>LLM: transcript forwarded
    LLM-->>Main: tool_call: music_search({ query: "Future" })
    Main->>Main: YouTube + SoundCloud search (parallel)
    Main-->>LLM: tool_result: [{ id: "youtube:abc", title: "..." }]
    LLM-->>Main: tool_call: music_queue_add({ tracks: ["youtube:abc"] })
    Main-->>LLM: tool_result: { ok: true }
    LLM-->>Main: tool_call: music_play({ index: 0 })

    Main->>Main: playVoiceQueueTrackByIndex()
    Main->>Main: requestPlayMusic() → playMusicViaDiscord()
    Main-->>Sub: IPC: { type: "music_play", url }
    Sub->>Sub: resetPlayback() — kill voice stream
    Sub->>YT: spawn yt-dlp -o - <url>
    Sub->>FF: spawn ffmpeg -f ogg -c:a libopus
    YT->>FF: raw audio (pipe)
    FF->>Sub: Ogg/Opus stream (pipe)
    Sub->>Sub: createAudioResource(StreamType.OggOpus)
    Sub->>Sub: audioPlayer.play(resource)
    Sub->>DV: Opus packets (UDP)
    DV->>User: Music audio

    Main->>Main: haltSessionOutputForMusicPlayback()
    Note over Main: Clears voice state (botTurnOpen,<br/>pending responses, barge-in)<br/>WITHOUT sending stop_playback IPC

    Note over Sub: Track ends naturally
    Sub->>Sub: AudioPlayer → Idle
    Sub-->>Main: IPC: { type: "music_idle" }
    Sub->>Sub: armVoicePlayback("music_idle")
    Note over Sub: Fresh PcmJitterBuffer created,<br/>ready for next voice response

    Note over User: "Can you pause that?"
    User->>Main: voice turn → LLM
    LLM-->>Main: tool_call: music_pause()
    Main-->>Sub: IPC: { type: "music_pause" }
    Sub->>Sub: audioPlayer.pause()

    Note over User: "Resume the song"
    User->>Main: voice turn → LLM
    LLM-->>Main: tool_call: music_resume()
    Main-->>Sub: IPC: { type: "music_resume" }
    Sub->>Sub: audioPlayer.unpause()
